<br>
Finally they all settled down and turned their attention to the old one.<br>
<br>
Without preamble he began.<br>
<br>
&quot;In the beginning there were two.  They were all that were.  One sought to bring order to the universe and was called Law.  The other sought to destroy what was made and was called Chaos.  Their conflict ebbed and flowed for more time than even the gods could fathom.  Finally the one who sought order made a plan.  He would put shape and structure to his realm while trapping the one who sowed chaos.  <br>
<br>
The plan almost worked.  Law released his essence into the universe and from this sprang the elder gods.  At the same time he sprung his trap on Chaos to lock him away from Law's creation.  Chaos was caught in the trap but before it could fully imprison him he too released his essence into the universe.  This spread the seeds of change and destruction among the newly born gods.<br>
<br>
Law and Chaos still exist.  Chaos is locked in his prison and Law is the key.  The Elder Gods gave onto Vesheen the task of guarding The Key.  They knew if Chaos was to escape then the war would begin again and it would destroy all that was.  Vesheen in turn placed us, her brood on this small world and gave us The Key to guard.  We must remain always alert.  The prison is imperfect and Chaos can still influence the world with the echo of change.  It was his doing that caused the other Gods to bring the others here.  We must now not only guard The Key but fight the other races.<br>
<br>
That is why we are here and you must never forget your this most important duty.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that the old one ceased to speak and his young students quietly slithered out of the chamber.  Once all were gone, a slightly older wyrm entered.<br>
<br>
&quot;Forgive me old one but we need you to come to the Sanctum at once.&quot;<br>
<br>
Very little could stir the old dragon to action but anything to do with the Sanctum was one of them.  Outrunning the younger dragon easily, the old one entered the Sanctum to see two acolytes staring at the large irregular crystal that floated and spun in the middle of the room.  this was The Key.  Upon moving closer he saw what had triggered the urgent summons.   Deep inside, barely perceptible by anyone other than a dragon, was a tiny crack.<br>
<br>
He felt a strange sensation and he could not remember what it was.  Then he realized.  It had been eons since he had felt it.  He was afraid.  He was afraid down to the core of his soul.  And worse, he had no idea what to do. <p><font face="lucida handwriting, arial" color="006800" size=+2><b>Radgen Warenherz</font></b><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="675f00" size=+1><b>Ranger of Karana</font><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="blue" size=+1>The Eternal Conclave</font></b><br><img src=http://home.att.net/~h.e.williamson/source/tiger_run_md_clr.gif>
