<br>
He had left the Missed Note with barely a word,  only a note expressing his regret to Sasi.  It was there that the closest thing to friends he had were but he could not explain his reasons even to them.  He wouldn’t even know where to start.  He had felt the loss of control building for years.  He could not allow himself to get involved any deeper in any “causes” or “crusades”.<br>
<br>
Now as to the intruder.   Obviously it was not a giant, he had chosen this shallow cave specifically because it was at the head of a very narrow ravine.  The Mountain Giants could not even approach his home.  The goblins, sarnaks and others, while quick to attack him if they caught him out and about, never tried to track down his den.  When he cautiously opened the door and a almost forgotten aroma met his nostrils he relaxed.  It had taken longer that expected but his oldest friend had found him again.<br>
<br>
‘You know it can be dangerous to enter a man’s home uninvited around these parts.”  he said as he nonchalantly walked in.<br>
<br>
“Hmph...  that is the pot calling the kettle black.”  His guest retorted, though Radgen did not know why he would say that.<br>
<br>
Quickly dressing the rabbit he had snared Radgen continued. “Well old man, I expected you so show up sooner,  I’ve been in this world for years already.”<br>
<br>
 He heard his guest shift in his chair before the “Old man” responded.  “True, I fully expected you to already be at the head of some great army, with half the world under your thumb and the other half tottering on the edge.”<br>
<br>
That barb hit a little to close to home.  He knew better than anyone his unfortunate tendency to destroy everything around him.  “I am tired old man.  All I want to do is live a quiet life and pray that the next time I die, it is the last time.  No more new worlds, no more wars, no more crusades.”<br>
<br>
When Radgen looked up from his tasks he saw the old man staring at him.  His eyes were filled with profound sorrow.  “This isn’t the last world is it old man?” he asked.<br>
<br>
“No it isn’t.,  Before you ask how I know, get us a drink.  We will need it.”<br>
<br>
