<br>
&quot;In the world I am from I am well known and held in great respect and/or fear.  So much so that all any one has to do is mention &quot;The Wizard&quot;, The Sorcerer&quot; or 'The Old Man&quot; and everyone knows who they are talking about.  I am just a man but I have found myself with a great talent for meddling. <br>
<br>
Not everyone appreciates my ummm... efforts.  I live alone in an isolated tower in the wilderness, nothing but a small hamlet nearby.  My defenses are formidable.  They have to be.  There are beings whose power rivals the gods, who have reason to dislike me.  <br>
<br>
So it is needless to say I was taken aback when one day you waltzed right into my study without warning, plopped yourself down on a stool and propped your feet up on my desk.'<br>
<br>
Radgen opened his mouth to interrupt but the Old Man held up a hand to stop him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now I know you don't remember this.  It is because for you, it has not happened yet.  You figured out that your curse was sending you to one world after another but I don't think you realized that you are also jumping around in time.  The first time you met me was back before you were cursed, but the first time I met you on the other hand, has not happened for you yet.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Old Man let that sink in a bit.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now I did not try to blast you out of that stool you had so nonchalantly sat in cause you had immediately got my curiosity going.  I now realize that was exactly what you were trying to do.  For the next hour you vaguely referred to our friendship, though I knew nothing of it at the time, you seemed to be saying you simply stopped in to see an old friend.  Shortly there after you left.<br>
<br>
Obviously I dropped everything else I had been working on.  I had to find out who and what you were.  At first my confusion simply grew.  All I could find out was that you were a mercenary captain, A very good and honorable one but nothing really special.  Finally a powerful divination spell I cast revealed your curse and the general nature of it.  Painstakingly I tracked down all the worlds and times you had been, till I found the &quot;start&quot;.  I determined to travel to as many of these times and places to get to know you, to try and fathom what you were up to.  The rest is history so to speak.  I have gotten to know you and like you said that first day, we have become friends.&quot;<br>
<br>
After the Old Man had stopped for a bit Radgen spoke up.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ok I always knew that there was a reason you seemed to be tagging along on my enforced journey, now tell me, did you lean what you wanted?&quot;<br>
<br>
Again the sadness showed clearly in the Old Man's eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes I have.  In some ways you are exceedingly normal.  You are not an angel and you are not a devil.  But I have seen you take actions that would make a devil think twice and an angel wonder at the depth of your generosity and selflessness.  You are walking proof that every man has the potential to be a monster or a saint.  You have been both.  <br>
<br>
This is not much for concern except that you are a naturally talented tactician, both politically and militarily.  Add to that literally centuries of experience and a drive to change the world around you and it makes you one of the most dangerous beings I have ever met.  <br>
<br>
I now realize that your visit to me so long ago was calculated to get me out of the way for a bit.  I am hopping times here but a little time will pass on my home world before I can return.  You have something planned and you know that whatever it is, I will oppose it.  Like I said we are friends and I think that was your way of avoiding yet again being on the other side of a battlefield from another person you care about.<br>
<br>
Yes I now realize I was being manipulated but I also know there was no malice in it.  Besides I am in no position to complain about manipulating people.&quot;<br>
<br>
Now the Old Man turned a deep stare on Radgen and finished.<br>
<br>
&quot;My only concern now is, I don't know who it was who showed up in my study.  Radgen the monster or Radgen the saint?&quot;<br>
<br>
With that Radgen got up pulled 3 more bottle down off the self.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know about you Old Man but I feel the need to get very drunk.&quot;<br>
<br>
Holding out his glass for a refill, the Old man replied.<br>
<br>
&quot;I completely agree.&quot; <p><font face="lucida handwriting, arial" color="006800" size=+2><b>Radgen Warenherz</font></b><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="675f00" size=+1><b>Ranger of Karana</font><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="blue" size=+1>Diamond Circle</font></b><br><img src=http://home.att.net/~h.e.williamson/source/tiger_run_md_clr.gif>
